    <title>diffpy.pdfgetx: Advanced Programs for Converting Powder Diffraction Data into Total Scattering Pair Distribution Functions</title>
    <link href="https://www.huaecho.cn/Tools/diffpy-pdfgetx/2230252193.html"/>
    <id>https://www.huaecho.cn/Tools/diffpy-pdfgetx/2230252193.html</id>
    <published>2023-07-15T11:17:45.000Z</published>
    <updated>2024-04-16T16:59:47.346Z</updated>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;img src=&quot;https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/diff.pdfgetx3/cover/cover.png?imageMogr2/format/avif&quot; alt=&quot;Total Scattering Resource&quot; title=&quot;Total Scattering Resource&quot; width=&quot;50%&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;diffpy.pdfgetx3 is an advanced and powderful software for converting &lt;strong&gt;Powder Diffraction&lt;/strong&gt; data to Total Scattering atomic &lt;strong&gt;Pair Distribution Funtions&lt;/strong&gt;. In addtion, it can also help us to extrat the PDFs from small-angle scattering(&lt;em&gt;SAS&lt;/em&gt;). The program include three command line programs PDFgetx3, PDFgetN3 and PDFgetS3 for processing &lt;strong&gt;X-ray&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Nertron&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Small-angle diffraction&lt;/strong&gt; data respectively.&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
